# Phishing Attack Incident Response Playbook

## 1. Preparation
- Educate employees on identifying phishing emails.
- Ensure email filtering and anti-phishing tools are active. 

## 2. Detection & Analysis
- Monitor email alerts for suspicious attachments or links.
- Analyze the email headers for anomalies.
- Use SIEM tools (e.g., Splunk) to check for any unusual login attempts.

## 3. Containment
- Block the sender's email address.
- Quarantine the affected email and any similar messages.
- Inform the affected user and reset their credentials.

## 4. Eradication & Recovery
- Remove any malicious software or links from affected systems.
- Conduct a full system scan using antivirus tools.
- Restore compromised data from backups if necessary.

## 5. Lessons Learned
- Remove the incident and update security awareness training. 
- Implement additional email security measures if needed. 
